balanceOf(address,uint256).notice: Returns the balance of an ERC1155 id on an account. WARNING: the balances returned by this method do not show negative fCash balances because only unsigned integers are returned. They are represented by zero here. Use `signedBalanceOf` to get a signed return value.

params.account: account to get the id for

returns._0: Balance of the ERC1155 id as an unsigned integer (negative fCash balances return zero)

balanceOfBatch(address[],uint256[]).notice: Returns the balance of a batch of accounts and ids. WARNING: negative fCash balances are represented as zero balances in the array.

params.accounts: array of accounts to get balances for
params.ids: array of ids to get balances for

returns._0: Returns an array of unsigned balances
